# Foyer Manager — Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Frontend : React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind v4
- Backend  : Node.js + Hono + TypeScript
- ORM      : Prisma
- Database : PostgreSQL
- Tests    : Vitest (unit) + Supertest (API)

## Monorepo Structure
apps/
├── web/          ← React frontend
└── api/          ← Node.js backend
packages/
└── types/        ← Shared TypeScript types

## Git — Conventional Commits
Format : <type>(<scope>): <description>
Types  : feat | fix | chore | docs | refactor | test
Scopes : web | api | types | infra
Examples:
  feat(api): add expense split endpoint
  fix(web): fix debt calculation
  chore(infra): update docker compose config

## Code Rules
- Strict TypeScript: no `any`, no `as unknown`
- Input validation: Zod required on all API endpoints
- Business logic in apps/api/src/services/ only, never in routes
- React: functional components only
- No useEffect for business logic → use TanStack Query
- Shared types imported from `@foyer/types`, never redefined locally

## Cursor Rules
- Only modify files directly related to the current request
- Always ask before touching files outside the current scope
- Suggest a unit test with every new service function
- Never install dependencies without explicitly listing them

## Language
All code, comments, variable names, commit messages, branch names,
PR titles and descriptions must be written in English.
No French in the codebase.